folder: Dry Harbor Road & Woodhaven Boulevard, Queens, NY
original_title: Queens: Dry Harbor Road - Woodhaven Boulevard
text:
Dry Harbor Road, east side, just south of Woodhaven Boulevard, showing a road florist's shop.

P. L. Sperr

June 29, 1936

folder: Woodhaven Blvd & Dry Harbor Road, Queens, NY
original_title: Queens: Woodhaven Blvd - Dry Harbor Road
text:
Woodhaven Boulevard, at Dry Harbor Road, showing the hot houses and florist's house on the east side of the Boulevard.  Charles Lustgarten owned the 2 1/2-acre tract and nurseries in 1909.  The traffic is on Dry Harbor Road.  Note in view 3, the hammock near the florist's house.

P.L. Sperr

View 1: June 29, 1936
Views 2, 3: July 2, 1935
